snippet.textDisplay: That definitely is not the world's biggest forklift. Or a forklift really. That's a telescopic handler aka boom lift. The Kalmar DCG720-10LB forklift is the world's biggest and strongest lifting 72 tons. Your buddy says yours lifts 20,000 lbs (10 tons) and you blurt out 20 ton (40,000 lb.) lift capability. I believe yours is about a 5 ton (10,000 lb.). The forklift you lift is 9,000 lbs. Max lift ability of a boom lift is 14,000 lbs. (7 ton). Definitely off on this one. But looks like exaggerating and lying gets you views and paid well. So mission accomplished.
